title: Suspect in slaying of parents, aunt, arrested in New Orleans -
text:
JONESBOROUGH, Tenn. (AP) - A man accused of killing his parents and aunt has been captured in New Orleans.
Washington County Sheriff Ed Graybeal told the Johnson City Press ( http://bit.ly/1LrhiAH ) deputies were alerted to search the victims' Jonesborough home by a woman in California. She called 911 early Saturday to report Daniel Lee Henry told her he had killed his family.
Deputies found the bodies about 1:30 a.m. Graybeal said they had been shot in the head sometime on Friday.
Henry was quickly added to the Tennessee Bureau of Investigation's Most Wanted list.
The 38-year-old was arrested in New Orleans about 8:30 p.m. Saturday by the U.S. Marshals Service Task Force while staying at a hotel he had checked into under his own name.
A warrant charges Henry with three counts of first-degree murder.
Information from: Johnson City Press, http://www.johnsoncitypress.com
